<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-09T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-09T16:00:00-05:00" n="778" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d778">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">862.857 Hannover/38: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Panama</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-09T17:00:00-04:00">May 9,
                                    1940—5 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>56. Your 59, May 6, 4 p.m.<note n="42" xml:id="d778fn42">Not
                                printed.</note> The Department understands that the reply of the
                            Venezuelan Government concerning the <hi rend="italic">Hannover</hi>
                            incident is to the effect that the matter should be referred to the
                            Inter-American Neutrality Committee and that no communication should be
                            addressed to the British and German Governments in regard thereto.
                            Please endeavor to confirm this impression.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>